    "comment": "Rationale: Table S1 contains 452 proteins identified in PSD (detergent-resistant synaptic junctional proteins) preparations of rat and mouse brains.\nFor proteins coming from datasets derived from PSD (detergent-resistant synaptic junctions) preparations without defined selection / enrichment of the pre- or postsynaptic compartment we cannot assign these proteins to excitatory and/or inhibitory nor to the presynapse or / and postsynapse without further information.\nDPYL3 was found as Q26951.\n\n17/11/2017 Pim\n- Listed as \"dihydropyrimidinase-like 3; unc-33-like phosphoprotein [Mus musculus]\" in table S1.. Experimental description: Rodents: \"Rats or mice were euthanized by CO2 in compliance with New York University Medical Center's Institutional Animal Care and Use Committee,...\", p. 858",
